# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# C extensions
*.so

# Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
.venv1/

# PyCharm project files
.idea/

# VSCode files (just in case)
.vscode/

# Logs
*.log

# Python environment files
.env
*.env

# Mac and system files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Pip metadata
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/

# Data/cache
*.sqlite3
```

To use it:

1. Create a file in your project root named `.gitignore` (if not already there).
2. Paste the above content into it.
3. Save the file.Now Git will ignore all unnecessary or auto-generated files.

